#
# Summary (measured):
#   prefill: ~89-105 tok/s single stream (~53 tok/s per stream when 2 prefill
#            concurrently); slot prefix-cache reuse works (cache_n 1349/1361,
#            re-prefill 288.6 ms vs 15198.5 ms cold)
#   decode:  22.7 tok/s single stream short-ctx; 15.9 tok/s single at ~1.4k
#            ctx; 13.8 tok/s per stream with both slots decoding
#
# Rate derivation (recorded reasoning, also in the workload descriptions):
#   chat-short-cpu:  mean service ~= 2 s prefill (200 tok @ ~100 tok/s) +
#                    <=10 s decode (lognormal cap 384, median ~121 tok @
#                    ~14-22 tok/s; real model may EOS earlier) ~= <=12 s.
#                    2 slots => saturation near ~0.17 req/s. Chosen rate
#                    0.08 rps ~= 0.5 utilization; 600 s => ~48 requests.
#   shared-prefix-cpu: cold prefill ~15.7 s (1400 tok @ 89 tok/s), sharing
#                    requests ~4-6 s (suffix only, given cache reuse); decode
#                    ~160 tok @ ~14 tok/s ~= 11 s => ~16-28 s service.
#                    2 slots => saturation near ~0.07-0.12 req/s. Chosen rate
#                    0.04 rps ~= 0.5 utilization; 600 s => ~24 requests
#                    (deliberately small; wide CIs stated in the reports).
#
